    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>Thanks to the work of the Drupal security team, we released <a href="https://www.drupal.org/node/2336327">Drupal Commerce 7.x-1.10</a> on September 10 to address an information disclosure vulnerability. Last week we released a companion module to that update, <a href="https://www.drupal.org/project/commerce_username_update">Commerce Username Update</a>, to help administrators manage the username update the release requires. The new version also includes a handful of minor bug fixes and a new feature to better support free order notifications on the checkout form.</p>
<p><a href="https://drupalcommerce.org/blog/16726/updating-drupal-commerce-created-usernames">Read more</a> to learn more about the patched vulnerability and new feature.</p>
